The body of the late Olubadan of Ibadanland, Oba Saliu Adetunji, has arrived at the Popoyemoja Palace, Ibadan. His remains was conveyed in an ambulance of the University College Hospital (UCH), Ibadan. His body arrived at about 10:40am. Clerics were already at the palace for prayers.   JUST IN: Makinde mourns Olubadan of Ibadanland     BREAKING: Olubadan joins ancestors at 93     Man City move 11 points clear, Spurs close in on top four   - Advertisement - The Nation gathered that the late monarch might be buried today in accordance with Islamic rites. Oba Adetunji was aged 93. Sympathisers have besieged the palace to mourn the monarch.